{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"36fda6a0417be76e449a0a10e1e378f125ad093812618362e8c3e6d06c423bee","slug":"why-python","location":"/01-Before-You-Begin/01-why-python.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Why you should still learn Python (in the age of vibe coding and LLMs)","description":"Foundational Python knowledge ensures you’re not just a user of tools—you’re a creator, capable of solving real-world problems with precision and control. While LLMs and 'vibe coding' tools may result in faster code generation, foundational knowledge of Python is still needed to debug and optimize AI-generated code.","numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"thumbnail":"/learnpython//build/undefined","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"01-why-python.md","url":"/learnpython//build/01-why-python-ad0c9522763bd3d8377d96886d77737e.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"While LLMs (especially generic ones) can produce functional Python snippets, they often lack context-specific nuances and could be full of bugs. Grasp of the language is still essential for customizing, debugging, and/or optimizing AI-generated code.","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"key":"s7IqEN7wC7"}],"key":"Nl1beMSmte"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This is specially true if you are building large, complex, or production-ready solutions from scratch.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"bJdUZnqrFr"}],"key":"wgCFK8LOHS"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"tip","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"MAINTAIN AUTONOMY OF YOUR CODE","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"c6rz8X8Hr1"}],"key":"n1eOW9wV6x"},{"type":